1
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:36,953
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:43,209 --> 00:00:44,377
Good job!

3
00:00:45,294 --> 00:00:46,379
Catch me!

4
00:00:47,838 --> 00:00:48,839
Oh, gosh!

5
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:52,093
What was that about?
It's too sunny for that.

6
00:00:52,176 --> 00:00:55,012
Dad! I was getting in my feels!

7
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:57,932
Sorry, I guess
not even thunder can stop you.

8
00:00:58,140 --> 00:01:00,309
Forget it.
I don't want to take photos anymore.

9
00:01:00,643 --> 00:01:02,645
What? Where are you going?

10
00:01:24,208 --> 00:01:25,418
Hello?

11
00:01:26,377 --> 00:01:29,505
I'm Lee Ui-yeong.
We spoke on the phone earlier.

12
00:01:31,716 --> 00:01:32,883
Mr. Lee?

13
00:01:38,973 --> 00:01:40,224
Mr. Lee?

14
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:42,351
Mr. Lee.

15
00:01:43,811 --> 00:01:44,812
Oh, gosh!

16
00:01:46,022 --> 00:01:48,441
Oh, gosh, I'm so sorry!

17
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:52,236
I'm sorry!

18
00:01:56,365 --> 00:01:57,491
Tae-seop!

19
00:01:58,367 --> 00:01:59,952
What are you doing here?

20
00:02:03,122 --> 00:02:04,123
Ui-yeong?

21
00:02:04,707 --> 00:02:06,167
Are you here to see me?

22
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:07,960
What? Me?

23
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:09,920
No, I'm here for work.

24
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:13,466
Are you...

25
00:02:13,549 --> 00:02:14,550
Lee Eun-ho?

26
00:02:15,509 --> 00:02:16,594
I'm the CEO of HOME.

27
00:02:16,677 --> 00:02:18,137
Oh, I see.

28
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:21,265
You're the CEO of HOME... What?

29
00:02:27,271 --> 00:02:29,899
Dad! There's a lady at Uncle's tent!

30
00:02:29,982 --> 00:02:31,984
What are you talking about?

31
00:02:34,654 --> 00:02:38,741
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 4

32
00:02:47,375 --> 00:02:48,459
Thank you.

33
00:03:03,766 --> 00:03:06,769
So, you two are both CEOs.

34
00:03:11,315 --> 00:03:12,650
What's your name?

35
00:03:13,984 --> 00:03:15,611
- Lee Sua.
- Sua...

36
00:03:15,778 --> 00:03:17,738
She's my daughter. She's seven.

37
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:22,660
So, did you really not know
that he was the CEO of HOME?

38
00:03:22,743 --> 00:03:25,413
- No.
- But you two went on a date.

39
00:03:27,456 --> 00:03:31,252
I run an interior designing business,
HOME, with a close friend.

40
00:03:31,335 --> 00:03:33,087
Interior design?

41
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:36,549
You must be very close to your friend.

42
00:03:37,341 --> 00:03:38,342
I guess so.

43
00:03:38,676 --> 00:03:40,094
- Oh...
- But you knew, right?

44
00:03:40,177 --> 00:03:42,805
- Yeah.
- You did?

45
00:03:43,013 --> 00:03:47,059
You could've given me a heads-up
via text or a quick call.

46
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:49,645
Things wouldn't have gotten so bad, then.

47
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:52,273
I thought you'd find out over time
if we worked together.

48
00:03:52,398 --> 00:03:54,358
But things didn't work out.

49
00:03:56,277 --> 00:03:57,570
Right, that's our fault.

50
00:03:57,653 --> 00:04:02,241
How did you even know
we were at this campsite?

51
00:04:02,366 --> 00:04:03,617
Did you stalk us?

52
00:04:03,701 --> 00:04:06,996
No, I did it the normal way,
like a regular person.

53
00:04:07,663 --> 00:04:08,914
Thank you.

54
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:12,042
Excuse me! Hello.

55
00:04:12,126 --> 00:04:14,754
Do you know where in Chuncheon
your boss is going?

56
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:17,798
- Sorry?
- I really need to talk to him.

57
00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:20,134
He'll regret it if he doesn't hear me out.

58
00:04:22,678 --> 00:04:23,888
I...

59
00:04:24,722 --> 00:04:26,307
wanted to tell you...

60
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:29,101
that I'm really sorry.

61
00:04:29,268 --> 00:04:30,686
This incident taught me

62
00:04:30,853 --> 00:04:35,232
that lack of respect comes
from being too lenient on myself.

63
00:04:35,399 --> 00:04:39,820
And I'm deeply sorry
about plagiarizing your design, too.

64
00:04:40,529 --> 00:04:44,617
I read the article.
The hotel didn't know better, either.

65
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:46,160
No, we didn't.

66
00:04:46,452 --> 00:04:49,163
But this wouldn't have happened

67
00:04:49,246 --> 00:04:51,957
if we did a proper background check.

68
00:04:53,209 --> 00:04:56,337
I didn't expect you to actually come.

69
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:57,880
That's very kind of you.

70
00:04:57,963 --> 00:05:00,966
- You're making me look bad now.
- Not at all.

71
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:05,346
Of course, Tae-seop was the one
staying up all night for the proposal.

72
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:07,640
But we'll accept...

73
00:05:09,016 --> 00:05:10,017
your apology.

74
00:05:10,309 --> 00:05:12,978
Thank you so much.

75
00:05:13,687 --> 00:05:15,022
It's time to get to the point

76
00:05:15,314 --> 00:05:16,899
and tell them I have a new proposal.

77
00:05:17,775 --> 00:05:20,152
I have to convince them
that they need to say yes

78
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:22,696
because I have the perfect solution
for everyone.

79
00:05:23,531 --> 00:05:25,783
I have to tell them, but...

80
00:05:27,535 --> 00:05:29,119
I know I should...

81
00:05:31,372 --> 00:05:32,748
I know, but...

82
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,626
I can't bring myself to start.

83
00:05:35,709 --> 00:05:37,670
Do you have anything else to say?

84
00:05:38,796 --> 00:05:39,880
Well...

85
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:44,176
I have a present!

86
00:05:44,635 --> 00:05:46,929
I brought it from the hotel.

87
00:05:47,137 --> 00:05:49,557
It's perfect for this table.

88
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:51,183
It's meat.

89
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,268
And Sua.

90
00:05:52,810 --> 00:05:54,937
I even prepared chocolate.

91
00:05:55,020 --> 00:05:56,105
Looks good, right?

92
00:05:58,482 --> 00:06:00,734
Yeah, it'd be rude to talk
about a new deal

93
00:06:00,818 --> 00:06:03,028
when I only just apologized.

94
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:06,115
I'll lighten the mood
and build a relationship first.

95
00:06:06,949 --> 00:06:09,201
I guess
we won't need to get groceries later.

96
00:06:09,285 --> 00:06:10,786
I'll tell them later.

97
00:06:11,328 --> 00:06:13,706
You've come a long way.
Join us for dinner.

98
00:06:15,374 --> 00:06:17,585
Is there anything I can help you with?

99
00:06:17,668 --> 00:06:20,087
Oh, not at all! Just have a seat.

100
00:06:20,170 --> 00:06:21,589
We can't make you work.

101
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:23,257
Here.

102
00:06:23,340 --> 00:06:26,218
So, what's your plan now?

103
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:30,306
You were waiting for her text.

104
00:06:33,684 --> 00:06:36,896
Take a walk by the river
and get some fresh air.

105
00:06:36,979 --> 00:06:38,105
I'll take these.

106
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:41,233
FIREWOOD AVAILABLE FOR SALE

107
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:48,490
Things are pretty much sorted over here.

108
00:06:48,741 --> 00:06:50,159
Good luck, Ui-yeong!

109
00:06:55,372 --> 00:06:57,458
- Hyun-min.
- Yeah?

110
00:06:57,958 --> 00:07:01,045
I guess I won't be landing
a permanent contract, right?

111
00:07:03,797 --> 00:07:06,425
Well, nobody knows yet.
It's too soon to tell.

112
00:07:07,551 --> 00:07:09,428
How about a dinner? And some soju?

113
00:07:09,511 --> 00:07:10,930
Next time.

114
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:12,431
Sae-byeok

115
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:16,226
eat some good food, watch good movies,
and don't think about this too much

116
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:17,811
over the weekend.

117
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:22,149
Nobody knows what's coming ahead.

118
00:07:22,858 --> 00:07:24,443
- Okay.
- It'll be fine.

119
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:42,086
Sua, let me film it for you.

120
00:07:42,294 --> 00:07:43,462
It's okay.

121
00:07:44,296 --> 00:07:45,798
You don't even know how good I am.

122
00:07:45,881 --> 00:07:47,591
I'm a great videographer.

123
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:50,302
What do you want? A vertical shot?
A close-up?

124
00:07:50,386 --> 00:07:52,388
Or a performance video?

125
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:55,432
You know your videos.

126
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:58,102
Just make me look lean, then.

127
00:07:59,561 --> 00:08:02,898
Play with me if you like it, okay?

128
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:04,274
- Okay.
- Okay!

129
00:08:07,403 --> 00:08:08,570
You want to look lean?

130
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:11,907
You look like a model!

131
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:14,576
Maybe it can be better.

132
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:16,829
Hold on.

133
00:08:22,918 --> 00:08:23,961
Come with me.

134
00:08:25,504 --> 00:08:26,672
Alright.

135
00:08:27,423 --> 00:08:28,841
Perfect. Look at me.

136
00:08:29,466 --> 00:08:30,718
You look so cute!

137
00:08:31,385 --> 00:08:32,386
You like it?

138
00:08:33,971 --> 00:08:36,140
It's perfect for today's weather!

139
00:08:38,225 --> 00:08:40,853
Turn around and look! Right on.

140
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:43,647
Perfect.

141
00:08:45,899 --> 00:08:48,402
This way, to the flowers! Yeah!

142
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:51,488
Come a bit closer.

143
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:55,993
Right there. Perfect!

144
00:08:56,118 --> 00:08:57,202
You want to see it?

145
00:08:57,286 --> 00:08:58,787
Check it. You like it?

146
00:08:58,871 --> 00:08:59,872
I do.

147
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:01,123
I'm good, right?

148
00:09:01,707 --> 00:09:03,042
It's Uncle!

149
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,126
Uncle!

150
00:09:20,517 --> 00:09:21,894
UNFORTUNATELY, YOU HAVE NO NEW MESSAGES

151
00:09:21,977 --> 00:09:23,771
28 PEOPLE LIKE YOU!

152
00:09:23,854 --> 00:09:25,439
YOU FREE TODAY?

153
00:09:26,982 --> 00:09:28,650
I'm all moisturized

154
00:09:29,318 --> 00:09:31,028
but there's nobody to see!

155
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:36,033
I'm not in the mood for more swipes.

156
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:40,162
Should I just read some cartoons?

157
00:09:50,672 --> 00:09:52,883
BIG DISCOUNTS

158
00:09:52,966 --> 00:09:54,927
I'd like to buy your cartoon books.

159
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:57,137
Are they outdated?

160
00:09:58,138 --> 00:10:00,015
It's really time to say goodbye.

161
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:03,352
I'll do my best
and charge her what you're worth.

162
00:10:04,311 --> 00:10:06,647
"Old"? You mean classic.

163
00:10:06,730 --> 00:10:09,525
They're masterpieces
that can inspire people anytime.

164
00:10:12,653 --> 00:10:14,655
Does it also have
a lot of handsome characters?

165
00:10:15,864 --> 00:10:18,408
Yeah, the illustrations are insane.

166
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:25,040
Okay, can we meet today, then?
I want to see them quickly.

167
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:26,875
I'll check them in person and pay.

168
00:10:27,292 --> 00:10:28,377
Today?

169
00:10:29,336 --> 00:10:31,338
She's about to read
the best cartoons ever.

170
00:10:34,466 --> 00:10:35,717
Okay!

171
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:41,390
Ui-yeong, what do you like to put
in your hot pot?

172
00:10:41,807 --> 00:10:44,560
I like glass noodles and yubu. And you?

173
00:10:44,768 --> 00:10:47,187
I like snow fungus and dried tofu.

174
00:10:47,479 --> 00:10:49,189
- Really?
- Sua!

175
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:51,441
Did you just call her by her name?

176
00:10:52,901 --> 00:10:54,403
I thought you were shy!

177
00:10:54,486 --> 00:10:55,571
No.

178
00:10:57,865 --> 00:11:00,159
Are you preparing dinner, Tae-seop?

179
00:11:00,701 --> 00:11:01,743
Yeah.

180
00:11:02,286 --> 00:11:03,287
Here, Sua.

181
00:11:04,997 --> 00:11:06,206
Put them there.

182
00:11:11,295 --> 00:11:12,462
I can help you carry some.

183
00:11:28,478 --> 00:11:31,440
How did he know my flats were wet?

184
00:11:45,704 --> 00:11:47,998
Good job.

185
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:53,212
These are so fresh.

186
00:11:53,962 --> 00:11:56,965
My Sua's all grown.

187
00:11:57,466 --> 00:11:58,467
Look.

188
00:12:11,355 --> 00:12:13,148
- Are you okay?
- Oh, gosh.

189
00:12:13,857 --> 00:12:15,067
Give it to me. I'll do it.

190
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:16,151
Okay.

191
00:12:18,362 --> 00:12:20,530
Sorry, I just wanted to help.

192
00:12:21,406 --> 00:12:23,992
I know you feel bad, but just have a seat.

193
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:25,577
This is fire. It's dangerous.

194
00:12:25,661 --> 00:12:27,579
Yeah, Ui-yeong, come here.

195
00:12:37,798 --> 00:12:39,299
Give me my juice.

196
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:41,760
- You make it sound like I owe you.
- Thanks.

197
00:12:42,678 --> 00:12:44,263
One more.

198
00:12:44,763 --> 00:12:46,139
- "Please."
- Please.

199
00:12:54,439 --> 00:12:57,067
Ui-yeong, why is your face so red?

200
00:12:57,401 --> 00:12:58,443
Huh?

201
00:12:58,652 --> 00:13:00,404
You look like an apple.

202
00:13:00,737 --> 00:13:02,030
Oh, do I?

203
00:13:07,244 --> 00:13:08,245
It's just hot.

204
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:16,795
The meat is ready.

205
00:13:19,172 --> 00:13:21,258
- Dig in.
- Thanks.

206
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:25,137
- Is it good?
- Let's close our business.

207
00:13:27,889 --> 00:13:29,808
It's amazing!

208
00:13:29,891 --> 00:13:31,018
It just melts!

209
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:32,728
We have a lot of meat, so eat up.

210
00:13:33,770 --> 00:13:35,439
Eat with us first.

211
00:13:35,981 --> 00:13:37,357
Yeah, have some first.

212
00:13:38,025 --> 00:13:39,067
Here, Sua!

213
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:41,987
I don't want any. I'm not hungry.

214
00:13:42,070 --> 00:13:43,947
What? You can't ask for some later.

215
00:13:44,031 --> 00:13:45,574
I'm going to finish it all!

216
00:13:45,907 --> 00:13:47,117
- Huh?
- What?

217
00:13:48,952 --> 00:13:50,620
What a girl.

218
00:13:52,497 --> 00:13:54,708
She's going to get hungry at night.

219
00:13:54,791 --> 00:13:56,585
She had too many snacks earlier.

220
00:13:58,837 --> 00:14:00,839
What's Sua's favorite animal?

221
00:14:00,922 --> 00:14:02,758
Between bunnies, bears, and swans?

222
00:14:02,841 --> 00:14:04,718
She likes them all. Maybe bunnies?

223
00:14:04,801 --> 00:14:05,802
Bunnies?

224
00:15:05,570 --> 00:15:08,365
Ms. Lee Sua in the deluxe suite

225
00:15:08,573 --> 00:15:09,866
your room service is here.

226
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:13,412
I've prepared a mini-burger,
a perfect meal to eat in the tent.

227
00:15:23,296 --> 00:15:24,423
Here.

228
00:15:26,341 --> 00:15:27,801
Enjoy your food!

229
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:40,605
I'm here. I'm wearing a red hoodie.

230
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:02,335
Are you "Don't Give Up"?

231
00:16:02,711 --> 00:16:03,712
Oh.

232
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:05,672
It's "Don't Give Discounts."

233
00:16:05,755 --> 00:16:08,842
Because I don't give discounts, ever.

234
00:16:10,051 --> 00:16:11,094
- Sorry?
- So

235
00:16:11,386 --> 00:16:12,554
are you "Big Spender"?

236
00:16:12,637 --> 00:16:14,014
It's "Big Discounts."

237
00:16:14,681 --> 00:16:15,765
Oh.

238
00:16:22,898 --> 00:16:25,859
The deal's off the table
as soon as I find a booger.

239
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:29,154
I'm not like that.

240
00:16:29,237 --> 00:16:30,822
No need to lie.

241
00:16:31,114 --> 00:16:33,116
Who doesn't pick their noses?

242
00:16:38,371 --> 00:16:41,082
This isn't a library, alright?

243
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:45,212
I just get focused really easily, okay?

244
00:16:45,295 --> 00:16:47,214
Don't be so grumpy.

245
00:16:47,297 --> 00:16:50,091
I'll take all but the two ragged ones.

246
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:51,510
Give me a 10,000 won discount.

247
00:16:53,970 --> 00:16:55,972
That's nonsense.
This is a part of the set!

248
00:16:56,056 --> 00:16:58,725
And this scene...

249
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:00,852
from the series is

250
00:17:00,936 --> 00:17:03,605
what defines the whole series!

251
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:05,899
That's for me to decide.

252
00:17:05,982 --> 00:17:07,067
You know

253
00:17:07,150 --> 00:17:09,069
this guy.

254
00:17:09,819 --> 00:17:12,030
I'm reading the series
to see him play basketball.

255
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:16,076
Or give me a better deal.

256
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:17,410
Didn't you read my post?

257
00:17:17,827 --> 00:17:19,120
"No discounts."

258
00:17:30,257 --> 00:17:31,633
Gosh, my eyes sting.

259
00:17:32,842 --> 00:17:35,178
Fine, let's do it fair and square.

260
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:36,263
Fair and square?

261
00:17:36,721 --> 00:17:38,598
- So, you're not taking them?
- Hey!

262
00:17:39,432 --> 00:17:41,476
Since it's a basketball cartoon,
how about a basketball game?

263
00:17:41,601 --> 00:17:44,104
If I beat you,
give me a 10,000 won discount.

264
00:17:44,187 --> 00:17:46,523
If you win, I'll give you 10,000 won more.

265
00:17:47,274 --> 00:17:48,275
10,000 won?

266
00:17:52,445 --> 00:17:55,323
You want to play
a 1-on-1 game of basketball against me?

267
00:17:56,199 --> 00:17:57,784
What was that?

268
00:17:59,119 --> 00:18:02,080
We can play rock-paper-scissors
if you're scared.

269
00:18:02,163 --> 00:18:03,999
You're definitely scared.

270
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:10,380
Gosh, I'm scared for your defeat.

271
00:18:10,463 --> 00:18:12,007
Okay, I'm ready.

272
00:18:12,674 --> 00:18:14,092
You sure you won't regret it?

273
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:15,468
Deal.

274
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,557
This isn't basketball.

275
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:23,602
See?

276
00:18:24,102 --> 00:18:26,313
It says "Basketball."
It's a basketball game.

277
00:18:26,396 --> 00:18:28,356
Even little kids know.

278
00:18:29,941 --> 00:18:31,651
Give me 1,000 won for the game.

279
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:33,987
Come on.

280
00:18:38,366 --> 00:18:39,367
Okay.

281
00:18:42,370 --> 00:18:44,039
Watch what I do first, alright?

282
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:46,833
I'll go very easy on you.

283
00:19:11,775 --> 00:19:12,776
3 POINTS, TWICE

284
00:19:12,859 --> 00:19:13,860
TARGET SCORE: 20
USER SCORE: 39

285
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:16,863
Why is she scoring with every shot?

286
00:19:17,781 --> 00:19:19,240
TIME'S UP

287
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:21,201
Yeah!

288
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:24,412
You saw that? I got 145!

289
00:19:28,583 --> 00:19:29,584
Your turn.

290
00:19:30,251 --> 00:19:31,461
You can go.

291
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:39,678
I thought he didn't want to play.

292
00:19:39,761 --> 00:19:42,097
Alright, the left hand is
just for support.

293
00:19:45,725 --> 00:19:46,726
3 POINTS

294
00:19:47,936 --> 00:19:49,229
Why is he so good?

295
00:19:51,231 --> 00:19:52,899
What are you doing?

296
00:19:54,734 --> 00:19:56,361
Where are your manners?

297
00:19:56,444 --> 00:19:57,654
What are you talking about?

298
00:19:57,737 --> 00:20:00,031
We didn't say we couldn't block.

299
00:20:01,991 --> 00:20:05,537
Okay, using force isn't cheating, then.

300
00:20:08,206 --> 00:20:09,916
Focus!

301
00:20:26,349 --> 00:20:27,642
MY RECORD

302
00:20:27,726 --> 00:20:29,352
TOTAL SCORE: 129

303
00:20:32,981 --> 00:20:36,067
Fine, we always have to play three games.
Let's play another one.

304
00:20:36,693 --> 00:20:38,611
What else is here?

305
00:20:39,612 --> 00:20:40,780
I'm ready for anything.

306
00:20:40,864 --> 00:20:41,865
Come!

307
00:20:43,032 --> 00:20:45,076
Don't block my way!

308
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:47,370
Go that way!

309
00:20:55,128 --> 00:20:56,129
Just die!

310
00:21:03,803 --> 00:21:04,971
Alright!

311
00:21:08,892 --> 00:21:09,893
Drift!

312
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:13,521
Faster!

313
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:18,443
Did you see my power move?

314
00:21:18,651 --> 00:21:20,069
Hey, be respectful.

315
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:35,293
Humans are mere dots that last so briefly

316
00:21:35,376 --> 00:21:38,171
in this vast galaxy.

317
00:21:42,717 --> 00:21:46,721
Sua, I will allow you to have
marshmallows today.

318
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:49,265
- Really?
- Let's go!

319
00:22:06,866 --> 00:22:08,576
- Is it awkward?
- Sorry?

320
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:11,329
No, not at all.

321
00:22:14,165 --> 00:22:16,084
Oh, a shooting star! Did you see that?

322
00:22:16,167 --> 00:22:17,335
Make a wish! Quick!

323
00:22:17,418 --> 00:22:19,420
I hope Mom, Dad, Seung-jun, me

324
00:22:19,504 --> 00:22:22,215
Sua, Tae-seop, and Eun-ho will all be
happy and healthy.

325
00:22:22,298 --> 00:22:23,675
And please give me a raise.

326
00:22:23,758 --> 00:22:26,594
I haven't given up on dating,
so please bring me a good guy.

327
00:22:26,761 --> 00:22:29,389
That was a really long wish.

328
00:22:29,973 --> 00:22:32,475
You don't get to make wishes very often.

329
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,687
Did you make a wish?

330
00:22:38,231 --> 00:22:39,983
Did you wish for a wife?

331
00:22:40,066 --> 00:22:41,067
What?

332
00:22:41,901 --> 00:22:43,319
No, why would I do that?

333
00:22:43,403 --> 00:22:45,363
Remember what you asked me on our date?

334
00:22:45,905 --> 00:22:46,948
Our very first date.

335
00:22:47,866 --> 00:22:49,659
You have no idea how surprised I was.

336
00:22:51,411 --> 00:22:52,787
I asked that...

337
00:22:53,037 --> 00:22:54,205
since I'm older.

338
00:22:54,289 --> 00:22:56,082
I want to be
more intentional about dating.

339
00:22:56,165 --> 00:22:59,711
And I was also just trying to say
I was into you.

340
00:22:59,794 --> 00:23:01,170
But it just came out a bit...

341
00:23:04,257 --> 00:23:06,968
Oh, I didn't know that.

342
00:23:08,303 --> 00:23:11,806
Is that why
you went on another blind date?

343
00:23:12,015 --> 00:23:14,559
Because I scared you
with the marriage talk?

344
00:23:15,184 --> 00:23:16,603
I was surprised, for sure.

345
00:23:16,811 --> 00:23:19,856
But you seemed so chill about me
going on a date with someone else.

346
00:23:20,356 --> 00:23:23,484
I thought you weren't interested in me.

347
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:27,405
Oh, yeah, I did.

348
00:23:29,574 --> 00:23:30,909
Isn't it so odd?

349
00:23:31,576 --> 00:23:35,413
When you try to be extra considerate,
it drives people away.

350
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:39,125
And when you try
not to think about something

351
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:42,337
you think about it even more.

352
00:23:45,006 --> 00:23:47,300
I wanted to keep it formal with you today

353
00:23:48,301 --> 00:23:49,344
but to be honest

354
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:54,933
I can't stop thinking about you,
even in this moment.

355
00:24:10,823 --> 00:24:11,991
Ui-yeong!

356
00:24:12,075 --> 00:24:14,535
- This is so good!
- Thanks.

357
00:24:14,869 --> 00:24:15,912
Thanks.

358
00:24:16,871 --> 00:24:17,914
Here.

359
00:24:18,164 --> 00:24:19,332
Mine!

360
00:24:29,884 --> 00:24:31,594
He doesn't want to think about me

361
00:24:32,095 --> 00:24:34,305
but that makes him think about me more.

362
00:24:35,556 --> 00:24:37,266
I know what that means.

363
00:24:55,451 --> 00:24:57,954
That makes me hopeful

364
00:24:58,621 --> 00:25:00,623
despite knowing I ruined it all.

365
00:25:12,218 --> 00:25:13,302
She's sleeping.

366
00:25:18,224 --> 00:25:19,434
Watch your steps.

367
00:25:19,642 --> 00:25:20,977
I didn't know this was here.

368
00:25:23,229 --> 00:25:25,648
I'll quickly go and wash these.
You can tuck Sua in bed.

369
00:25:26,441 --> 00:25:29,152
Thanks so much.

370
00:25:42,373 --> 00:25:43,416
Hey.

371
00:25:44,083 --> 00:25:46,753
Let's invite her to stay the night here
if she's okay.

372
00:25:46,919 --> 00:25:48,463
You and I can share a tent

373
00:25:48,546 --> 00:25:50,381
and Ui-yeong can sleep with Sua.

374
00:25:50,923 --> 00:25:53,509
It's getting too dark
because we're in the mountains.

375
00:25:55,762 --> 00:25:57,722
Okay, I'd better tidy my tent, then.

376
00:26:15,531 --> 00:26:17,784
DAD AND UNCLE

377
00:26:20,495 --> 00:26:24,832
WOOD AND SPIRITS NIGHT
WHISKEY BRAND POP-UP PROPOSAL

378
00:26:35,593 --> 00:26:37,261
TEAM LEADER OH MYEONG-UN

379
00:26:37,637 --> 00:26:39,430
Oh, I forgot about this.

380
00:26:39,847 --> 00:26:41,974
Or maybe I didn't want to think about it.

381
00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:43,935
TEAM LEADER OH MYEONG-UN

382
00:26:45,394 --> 00:26:48,564
Hey, Ui-yeong. Did they say they'd do it?

383
00:26:48,648 --> 00:26:51,526
I'm still waiting for a good time to talk.

384
00:26:52,193 --> 00:26:54,695
I think we should talk about it
back in Seoul, though.

385
00:26:55,404 --> 00:26:57,115
It'll be better to talk to them properly

386
00:26:57,406 --> 00:26:59,158
in a proper meeting...

387
00:26:59,242 --> 00:27:02,745
Exactly. Why would you take a cab
to Chuncheon to apologize?

388
00:27:02,829 --> 00:27:05,873
And just see the end of it
if you're there already, anyway!

389
00:27:05,957 --> 00:27:07,792
Don't do a half-assed job, alright?

390
00:27:07,875 --> 00:27:09,418
- "Half-ass"?
- Listen.

391
00:27:09,502 --> 00:27:13,714
If they say no,
we just won't see their design, okay?

392
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:14,799
Hello?

393
00:27:15,591 --> 00:27:16,676
Can you hear me?

394
00:27:17,301 --> 00:27:18,469
Yes, I can.

395
00:27:18,761 --> 00:27:20,012
I can hear you clearly.

396
00:27:22,181 --> 00:27:23,516
Fine, I'll try to talk to them.

397
00:27:24,475 --> 00:27:26,644
That's why I'm here until this late,
anyway.

398
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:31,983
Okay.

399
00:27:41,742 --> 00:27:42,743
Nina!

400
00:27:43,202 --> 00:27:45,621
I resented you
and wished the worst for you.

401
00:27:45,705 --> 00:27:47,957
And I tore your letters and photos.

402
00:27:48,875 --> 00:27:50,334
But never for a moment

403
00:27:51,002 --> 00:27:53,254
did I ever forget

404
00:27:53,504 --> 00:27:55,089
that our souls were together.

405
00:27:59,427 --> 00:28:01,512
I cannot hate you, Nina.

406
00:28:09,437 --> 00:28:11,731
- Good work today, Ji-su.
- Good job.

407
00:28:12,023 --> 00:28:13,357
Great work, everyone.

408
00:28:13,441 --> 00:28:15,276
- Let's clean up and get a drink.
- Okay.

409
00:28:24,243 --> 00:28:25,286
About the after-party...

410
00:28:25,369 --> 00:28:28,206
We're going to the restaurant
we always go to near the park.

411
00:28:28,289 --> 00:28:29,332
No.

412
00:28:29,457 --> 00:28:30,917
Why don't we have a private one?

413
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:33,628
I want to get to know you better.

414
00:28:42,011 --> 00:28:45,431
You think you can become a good actor
when you don't value others' feelings?

415
00:28:46,515 --> 00:28:50,144
That was Eun-a's last performance.
She's not coming back anymore.

416
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:52,438
Another one? But she just joined.

417
00:28:53,356 --> 00:28:54,607
You know how it goes.

418
00:28:54,899 --> 00:28:56,692
It's all about love.

419
00:28:56,901 --> 00:28:59,445
She's been very close with Ji-su
for a while.

420
00:28:59,570 --> 00:29:03,157
It's like he's not even acting.
He just seduces every female lead.

421
00:29:03,241 --> 00:29:06,744
He seduces his partners and the audience.

422
00:29:07,161 --> 00:29:09,163
I was just looking out for her
as her partner.

423
00:29:09,247 --> 00:29:10,289
You heard me?

424
00:29:10,456 --> 00:29:12,124
That sounded more like a compliment.

425
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:13,876
I know!

426
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:15,503
Stop messing with us here

427
00:29:15,586 --> 00:29:18,339
and just go into acting
for movies and dramas!

428
00:29:18,422 --> 00:29:21,175
- Yeah.
- Directors are lined up to hire you!

429
00:29:21,759 --> 00:29:24,845
No, my life is hard enough as is.

430
00:29:29,141 --> 00:29:31,018
I don't feel like drinking anymore. Bye.

431
00:29:31,102 --> 00:29:33,479
Who's going to cook the meat for us, then?

432
00:29:33,854 --> 00:29:34,855
You hungry?

433
00:29:35,189 --> 00:29:38,401
I thought you were full
from talking all that crap about me.

434
00:29:38,484 --> 00:29:40,111
- Which table...
- I'll take them.

435
00:29:41,696 --> 00:29:43,364
Cook it for yourselves.

436
00:29:44,156 --> 00:29:46,158
And leave me alone for a while.

437
00:29:46,742 --> 00:29:49,537
Where are you going?
You live at the theater.

438
00:29:49,620 --> 00:29:50,830
Are you really leaving?

439
00:29:51,163 --> 00:29:52,999
I know you got fired from the restaurant!

440
00:30:31,912 --> 00:30:33,581
You've been here for a while.

441
00:30:33,873 --> 00:30:35,624
Do you need help?

442
00:30:35,875 --> 00:30:37,960
No, I'm fine.

443
00:30:38,669 --> 00:30:39,754
Here, take this.

444
00:30:42,798 --> 00:30:44,133
It smells great.

445
00:30:45,968 --> 00:30:46,969
Goodbye, then.

446
00:31:01,734 --> 00:31:04,236
LOOKING FOR PART-TIME BARISTA AND CLEANER
HOURS AND SCHEDULE NEGOTIABLE

447
00:31:10,701 --> 00:31:13,287
Director Jin is making this movie,
but it's a big secret.

448
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:16,248
The female lead is a gardener
who's going blind.

449
00:31:16,332 --> 00:31:19,293
She's waiting for her old lover,
who may not even return

450
00:31:19,377 --> 00:31:22,630
as she tends to her garden
full of poisonous plants.

451
00:31:23,798 --> 00:31:25,800
It's a romance movie
with a hint of thriller.

452
00:31:26,050 --> 00:31:27,093
So

453
00:31:27,843 --> 00:31:29,470
does Director Jin want to hire me?

454
00:31:30,262 --> 00:31:32,098
You said he's not sure
because of my rumors.

455
00:31:32,181 --> 00:31:35,184
Come on. Rumors mean nothing.

456
00:31:35,267 --> 00:31:36,727
It's not even official news.

457
00:31:36,894 --> 00:31:38,354
We booked a meeting.

458
00:31:38,437 --> 00:31:40,231
Just rest up for a few days at the hotel

459
00:31:40,356 --> 00:31:42,691
and meet him once you're refreshed.

460
00:31:42,775 --> 00:31:44,610
It's about time you return to Cannes!

461
00:31:47,738 --> 00:31:50,282
Oh? Can you stop the car for a sec?

462
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:54,453
Ji-su.

463
00:31:57,206 --> 00:31:59,250
You look even better than last time.

464
00:31:59,333 --> 00:32:00,793
How come you don't take my calls?

465
00:32:01,001 --> 00:32:03,087
I thought we were close enough
for phone calls.

466
00:32:04,422 --> 00:32:06,048
You don't need any money?

467
00:32:10,469 --> 00:32:13,222
How rude! He shouldn't do that
when an adult is talking!

468
00:32:13,556 --> 00:32:15,933
You want to go in for a bit?

469
00:32:16,434 --> 00:32:17,726
It's fine.

470
00:32:18,102 --> 00:32:19,603
He can't run from me forever.

471
00:32:21,355 --> 00:32:22,982
I'm tired. Let's head back.

472
00:32:26,819 --> 00:32:29,155
So, you want to make her go back now?

473
00:32:35,536 --> 00:32:36,537
Hey, Ui-yeong.

474
00:32:39,206 --> 00:32:42,042
You know, it's getting late.

475
00:32:42,126 --> 00:32:44,587
The last train is leaving soon.

476
00:32:44,795 --> 00:32:47,381
Why don't you drive her to the station?

477
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:49,300
I can't drive. I had beer.

478
00:32:49,592 --> 00:32:50,593
What?

479
00:32:53,721 --> 00:32:57,016
Why are you suddenly...

480
00:32:57,349 --> 00:32:58,726
Why are you really here?

481
00:33:00,060 --> 00:33:01,061
Sorry?

482
00:33:01,562 --> 00:33:04,857
Why did you stay here
and spend the whole day with us?

483
00:33:07,109 --> 00:33:08,903
Well...

484
00:33:10,654 --> 00:33:11,947
WOOD AND SPIRITS NIGHT

485
00:33:13,657 --> 00:33:15,201
You're not here to apologize.

486
00:33:16,243 --> 00:33:17,244
Tell me the truth.

487
00:33:18,037 --> 00:33:19,455
I'll give you one last chance.

488
00:33:22,541 --> 00:33:23,584
Oh, I...

489
00:33:25,169 --> 00:33:28,923
I wanted to apologize first.

490
00:33:30,966 --> 00:33:33,260
I wanted to talk about this proposal
another time.

491
00:33:35,262 --> 00:33:39,808
I came up with an idea
that'd benefit both parties.

492
00:33:40,434 --> 00:33:44,772
I'm sure you already have a lot of clients

493
00:33:45,606 --> 00:33:49,193
but you could promote your brand even more

494
00:33:49,693 --> 00:33:54,949
by collaborating with our hotel...

495
00:33:57,076 --> 00:33:58,202
Is that all?

496
00:33:58,661 --> 00:33:59,995
Should I call a cab for you?

497
00:34:03,165 --> 00:34:04,166
No.

498
00:34:06,669 --> 00:34:08,254
I can go alone.

499
00:34:10,923 --> 00:34:12,174
Sorry.

500
00:34:50,212 --> 00:34:52,548
Why are you so good at every game?

501
00:34:52,798 --> 00:34:54,174
Do you just play games all day?

502
00:34:54,258 --> 00:34:56,051
I'm just good at winning.

503
00:34:56,885 --> 00:34:57,886
You know what?

504
00:34:58,387 --> 00:35:01,015
Let me give you a tip
since I saved an extra 10,000 won.

505
00:35:01,265 --> 00:35:03,225
But I'm the one walking away with money.

506
00:35:04,184 --> 00:35:05,185
What is it?

507
00:35:05,269 --> 00:35:09,356
People who stick to the rules
can never beat people like me.

508
00:35:09,481 --> 00:35:11,275
Just run away when you see one, okay?

509
00:35:11,358 --> 00:35:13,861
What kind of a tip is that?

510
00:35:17,239 --> 00:35:20,034
Anyway, I hope we never meet again.

511
00:35:21,952 --> 00:35:22,953
Wait!

512
00:35:25,956 --> 00:35:28,500
You don't seem like you want to go yet.

513
00:35:28,834 --> 00:35:30,252
Why don't we make another deal?

514
00:35:32,463 --> 00:35:35,174
- What deal?
- This is too heavy.

515
00:35:35,257 --> 00:35:37,926
Help me carry it to my house,
and I'll give you that 10,000 won.

516
00:35:38,010 --> 00:35:39,678
It's a delivery fee.

517
00:35:59,406 --> 00:36:02,034
Sure, I guess it's heavy.

518
00:36:03,327 --> 00:36:04,912
You promised 10,000 won, okay?

519
00:36:11,502 --> 00:36:12,544
Come in.

520
00:36:22,137 --> 00:36:23,889
Did you know I was trying to seduce you?

521
00:36:24,223 --> 00:36:26,350
You kept making nonsensical excuses.

522
00:36:26,809 --> 00:36:28,352
I thought you might be.

523
00:36:28,769 --> 00:36:30,062
But here you are

524
00:36:30,229 --> 00:36:33,065
instead of running away?

525
00:37:34,209 --> 00:37:35,502
Is that all?

526
00:37:36,795 --> 00:37:37,796
Yeah.

527
00:38:34,561 --> 00:38:35,646
BUS TIMETABLE

528
00:38:36,271 --> 00:38:38,232
LAST BUS: 11 P.M.

529
00:38:40,692 --> 00:38:41,693
What?

530
00:38:42,236 --> 00:38:43,862
That was the last bus?

531
00:39:08,053 --> 00:39:09,054
Huh?

532
00:39:11,557 --> 00:39:14,017
Seriously? Not even the weather's helping?

533
00:39:22,526 --> 00:39:23,652
Oh, gosh!

534
00:39:26,363 --> 00:39:28,407
- Turn around and look!
- It's Uncle!

535
00:39:28,490 --> 00:39:29,491
Uncle!

536
00:39:31,076 --> 00:39:32,786
Oh, a shooting star! Did you see that?

537
00:39:32,870 --> 00:39:34,371
Make a wish! Quick!

538
00:39:37,583 --> 00:39:38,834
Sorry.

539
00:39:44,131 --> 00:39:46,008
Oh, no!

540
00:39:49,094 --> 00:39:50,929
Hurry! Let's head in!

541
00:39:52,389 --> 00:39:54,850
UI-YEONG

542
00:39:55,809 --> 00:39:57,644
The caller is unavailable.

543
00:39:57,728 --> 00:40:01,023
You will be directed to voicemail.

544
00:40:01,106 --> 00:40:02,524
Hey! Tae-seop!

545
00:40:03,233 --> 00:40:04,318
Tae-seop!

546
00:40:05,485 --> 00:40:07,821
It's pouring outside!

547
00:40:07,905 --> 00:40:09,740
It's raining cats and dogs!

548
00:40:09,823 --> 00:40:10,866
Oh, no, this is bad.

549
00:40:10,949 --> 00:40:12,159
We need to leave.

550
00:40:12,242 --> 00:40:14,328
The tent is only water resistant. Hurry!

551
00:40:14,411 --> 00:40:17,456
Pack up and go to the city with Sua first.

552
00:40:17,623 --> 00:40:18,624
What about you?

553
00:40:18,707 --> 00:40:19,875
I can't reach Ui-yeong.

554
00:40:20,375 --> 00:40:22,002
I have to make sure she's safe.

555
00:40:22,711 --> 00:40:26,214
- How? She's not even answering!
- No idea.

556
00:40:26,298 --> 00:40:27,799
- I'll call you later!
- Hey!

557
00:40:28,050 --> 00:40:29,343
Tae-seop!

558
00:40:29,927 --> 00:40:30,928
Hey!

559
00:40:44,775 --> 00:40:45,901
Man, it's getting cold.

560
00:40:56,119 --> 00:40:58,080
This has to be a punishment.

561
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:02,626
Ui-yeong!

562
00:41:04,127 --> 00:41:05,212
Ui-yeong!

563
00:41:06,463 --> 00:41:07,589
Ui-yeong!

564
00:41:08,131 --> 00:41:09,257
Ui-yeong!

565
00:41:10,634 --> 00:41:12,177
Ui-yeong... Oh!

566
00:41:27,109 --> 00:41:28,151
Oh, goodness.

567
00:41:28,902 --> 00:41:30,487
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

568
00:41:30,821 --> 00:41:34,658
Have you seen a lady about this tall?

569
00:41:35,117 --> 00:41:36,118
No.

570
00:41:36,201 --> 00:41:38,078
- Okay, thank you.
- Wait.

571
00:41:38,787 --> 00:41:40,622
It's too late to be out and looking.

572
00:41:40,706 --> 00:41:42,332
There are no more buses for the night

573
00:41:42,541 --> 00:41:44,501
and there are wild animals at night.

574
00:41:44,584 --> 00:41:46,128
- Wild animals?
- Yeah.

575
00:41:46,503 --> 00:41:49,131
Sir, could I borrow this bike?

576
00:41:49,214 --> 00:41:51,299
I'll just look around quickly
and return it.

577
00:41:51,383 --> 00:41:52,801
You're biking in this rain?

578
00:41:52,884 --> 00:41:53,885
Yeah.

579
00:41:55,595 --> 00:41:56,722
Okay, you can take it.

580
00:41:56,805 --> 00:41:57,889
Thank you, sir!

581
00:41:58,557 --> 00:41:59,725
By the way, I live...

582
00:41:59,808 --> 00:42:01,184
- down there...
- Thank you!

583
00:42:05,522 --> 00:42:06,940
Ui-yeong!

584
00:42:07,232 --> 00:42:08,483
Ui-yeong!

585
00:42:14,364 --> 00:42:15,574
Ui-yeong!

586
00:42:16,491 --> 00:42:17,701
Ui-yeong!

587
00:43:03,413 --> 00:43:04,414
Ui-yeong.

588
00:43:24,893 --> 00:43:26,019
Are you okay?

589
00:43:27,771 --> 00:43:29,231
Yeah, I'm fine.

590
00:43:30,148 --> 00:43:31,274
Did you...

591
00:43:32,067 --> 00:43:33,860
come here in this rain just for me?

592
00:43:36,363 --> 00:43:37,572
You're drenched.

593
00:43:48,125 --> 00:43:49,876
What are you like?

594
00:43:53,380 --> 00:43:54,422
Sorry?

595
00:43:54,881 --> 00:43:56,133
How would you like me...

596
00:43:57,551 --> 00:43:59,344
to remember you?

597
00:44:02,180 --> 00:44:06,309
Our timing was always bad,
as if we were cursed.

598
00:44:11,815 --> 00:44:13,900
What you've seen of me...

599
00:44:15,610 --> 00:44:17,571
I can't say none of that's who I am.

600
00:44:21,575 --> 00:44:23,702
The only thing I can do here is

601
00:44:23,827 --> 00:44:26,788
to be honest to the core.

602
00:44:26,872 --> 00:44:30,625
But that's not all of me.

603
00:44:32,377 --> 00:44:35,297
And I want to show you
those other sides of me.

604
00:44:38,466 --> 00:44:39,718
Please give me...

605
00:44:40,719 --> 00:44:42,554
some time.

606
00:44:51,605 --> 00:44:59,529
GOSEONG 1-RI

607
00:45:32,812 --> 00:45:33,897
Tae-seop

608
00:45:35,273 --> 00:45:37,984
thanks for coming to look for me.

609
00:45:40,487 --> 00:45:42,656
I'll be good to you
and show you how grateful I am.

610
00:45:43,740 --> 00:45:47,494
You sound like a politician
on a comeback tour.

611
00:45:49,579 --> 00:45:50,664
And...

612
00:45:51,748 --> 00:45:53,500
not all of what you've shown me was bad.

613
00:45:59,673 --> 00:46:02,634
I'm glad the rain's stopped.

614
00:46:24,155 --> 00:46:26,783
Why are we back here?
I checked where we were going.

615
00:46:26,866 --> 00:46:29,661
Let's head in for now.
It's getting dangerous.

616
00:46:30,412 --> 00:46:31,579
Wait.

617
00:46:31,997 --> 00:46:33,873
Are you religious?

618
00:46:34,332 --> 00:46:35,333
Huh?

619
00:46:36,042 --> 00:46:39,004
I will be from today on if I have to.

620
00:46:40,255 --> 00:46:41,256
Amen.

621
00:47:00,900 --> 00:47:03,653
Dear Master Lord

622
00:47:04,529 --> 00:47:07,866
was all of this your plan?

623
00:47:14,080 --> 00:47:16,750
Please help us just for the day.

624
00:47:18,001 --> 00:47:19,669
We won't cause any trouble.

625
00:47:20,795 --> 00:47:21,921
Amen.

626
00:47:23,298 --> 00:47:24,382
Ui-yeong.

627
00:47:32,640 --> 00:47:33,767
Thanks.

628
00:47:46,780 --> 00:47:49,407
We won't be punished for coming in here

629
00:47:49,783 --> 00:47:51,659
when we're not Catholic, right?

630
00:47:51,910 --> 00:47:52,952
Come on.

631
00:47:54,371 --> 00:47:55,830
Probably not.

632
00:47:57,374 --> 00:48:00,585
But let's leave early morning
before anyone comes.

633
00:48:01,461 --> 00:48:02,545
Let's do that.

634
00:48:06,925 --> 00:48:07,926
Are you cold?

635
00:48:08,426 --> 00:48:11,471
No, I'm much warmer than earlier.

636
00:48:12,680 --> 00:48:14,432
Maybe it's because you have long hair.

637
00:48:15,350 --> 00:48:17,018
It's still completely wet.

638
00:48:17,435 --> 00:48:20,855
Can you turn around for a sec?

639
00:48:22,774 --> 00:48:24,317
It'll dry in time.

640
00:48:25,068 --> 00:48:26,694
That'll take forever. Come here.

641
00:49:04,399 --> 00:49:06,109
Sorry.

642
00:49:06,943 --> 00:49:08,027
It's okay.

643
00:49:08,611 --> 00:49:09,904
Your hands are warm.

644
00:49:56,493 --> 00:49:57,994
Is this okay?

645
00:50:10,173 --> 00:50:12,675
If this is a sin

646
00:50:13,426 --> 00:50:15,011
I'll repent later.

647
00:50:46,584 --> 00:50:48,545
You have to ring the bell later, okay?

648
00:50:48,628 --> 00:50:51,422
Okay. When are you ringing it, then?

649
00:50:51,506 --> 00:50:53,258
One day, probably.

650
00:50:53,466 --> 00:50:54,509
I see.

651
00:50:58,972 --> 00:51:00,431
Bring Father here.

652
00:51:07,689 --> 00:51:09,774
They don't seem
like they're here for a service.

653
00:51:10,108 --> 00:51:11,859
No, look! They're clearly here to sleep.

654
00:51:19,242 --> 00:51:21,369
Oh? She just opened her eyes.

655
00:51:29,294 --> 00:51:30,545
Wake up, Tae-seop.

656
00:51:36,676 --> 00:51:40,722
Oh? Are you the priest here?

657
00:51:42,765 --> 00:51:43,933
Hello.

658
00:51:44,267 --> 00:51:46,811
You really came back, huh?

659
00:51:47,145 --> 00:51:48,438
Welcome.

660
00:51:48,521 --> 00:51:50,857
Do you know our Father?

661
00:52:05,288 --> 00:52:06,289
He’s handsome.

662
00:52:06,539 --> 00:52:07,957
Maybe we should've just left.

663
00:52:08,041 --> 00:52:09,167
Excuse me.

664
00:52:09,834 --> 00:52:12,962
If you're a guest at the church,
you're also my guest.

665
00:52:13,338 --> 00:52:15,214
I can't let you leave on an empty stomach.

666
00:52:15,882 --> 00:52:16,966
Thank you.

667
00:52:25,308 --> 00:52:26,809
It's so good.

668
00:52:27,268 --> 00:52:30,438
The sisters made the jam
using berries in the forest

669
00:52:30,521 --> 00:52:32,774
and I roasted the coffee beans

670
00:52:32,857 --> 00:52:35,276
on a cauldron lid.

671
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:36,819
No wonder it's so good.

672
00:52:36,903 --> 00:52:38,780
The coffee is so aromatic. It's amazing.

673
00:52:38,863 --> 00:52:40,657
- I guess it suits your taste.
- Yes.

674
00:52:40,782 --> 00:52:43,451
If you like it, try coming to our church.

675
00:52:46,454 --> 00:52:49,248
I think I might've become
a little faithful last night.

676
00:52:50,083 --> 00:52:51,292
Did you sleep well?

677
00:52:51,376 --> 00:52:53,503
You must be sore
from sleeping on a wooden bench.

678
00:52:53,711 --> 00:52:57,006
No, we would've been in serious trouble
if not for the church.

679
00:52:57,090 --> 00:52:58,174
Thank you so much.

680
00:52:58,925 --> 00:53:00,760
The church is always open.

681
00:53:01,761 --> 00:53:02,929
By the way

682
00:53:03,554 --> 00:53:04,889
how do you know each other?

683
00:53:05,264 --> 00:53:08,142
This quiet guy seemed
really worried about you.

684
00:53:08,434 --> 00:53:10,520
Is he your boyfriend?

685
00:53:10,603 --> 00:53:12,355
No, it's nothing like that.

686
00:53:13,231 --> 00:53:15,525
We're just acquaintances.

687
00:53:15,608 --> 00:53:16,693
"Acquaintances"?

688
00:53:26,703 --> 00:53:29,414
Sure, we're not friends
or work colleagues.

689
00:53:30,248 --> 00:53:33,126
I guess we're technically acquaintances.

690
00:53:33,584 --> 00:53:36,879
But we kissed! With a witness present!

691
00:53:42,552 --> 00:53:46,639
Eun-ho and Sua slept in the city.
They just checked out.

692
00:53:46,973 --> 00:53:49,726
We can drive you back to Seoul.

693
00:53:51,018 --> 00:53:53,980
Oh, it's fine. I can just take the train.

694
00:53:55,356 --> 00:53:57,233
You'll have a lot of explaining to do.

695
00:53:58,151 --> 00:54:01,988
About how you found me and where we slept.

696
00:54:03,281 --> 00:54:05,450
Oh, that's true.

697
00:54:25,845 --> 00:54:26,888
Hey

698
00:54:28,055 --> 00:54:29,182
about yesterday...

699
00:54:35,396 --> 00:54:37,440
- Sorry?
- About yesterday...

700
00:54:43,654 --> 00:54:46,574
You can return my hoodie next time.

701
00:54:49,327 --> 00:54:50,453
Oh.

702
00:54:51,412 --> 00:54:52,413
Sure.

703
00:54:53,998 --> 00:54:57,126
I'll make sure to wash it very clean

704
00:54:57,627 --> 00:54:59,212
before returning it to you.

705
00:55:40,378 --> 00:55:41,671
Row 26.

706
00:55:43,297 --> 00:55:44,298
There it is.

707
00:56:53,784 --> 00:56:55,036
What are you doing?

708
00:56:56,203 --> 00:56:58,039
It's my first time free riding.

709
00:56:58,331 --> 00:57:00,750
Is the fine ten times the ticket price
or something?

710
00:57:15,139 --> 00:57:17,308
It's still drizzling.

711
00:57:18,184 --> 00:57:20,478
But it looks like it'll clear up soon.

712
00:57:21,729 --> 00:57:23,272
Dad, where's Uncle?

713
00:57:23,356 --> 00:57:25,191
I think he found Ui-yeong.

714
00:57:25,775 --> 00:57:28,402
They finally met
without missing each other this time.

715
00:57:28,694 --> 00:57:30,154
I thought they had a fight.

716
00:57:30,237 --> 00:57:32,448
Fights sometimes lead to love.

717
00:57:33,616 --> 00:57:35,201
I think they'll work things out soon.

718
00:57:52,885 --> 00:57:54,929
Back in the day, at churches

719
00:57:56,430 --> 00:58:00,309
they offered to hide those on the run
or political prisoners.

720
00:58:10,236 --> 00:58:11,278
Ui-yeong?

721
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:08,002
Please pay for his ticket here.

722
00:59:08,085 --> 00:59:09,170
Okay.

723
00:59:13,132 --> 00:59:14,133
Thank you.

724
00:59:35,196 --> 00:59:38,741
MODU IT

725
00:59:50,294 --> 00:59:51,545
Man, it's cold.

726
00:59:51,712 --> 00:59:53,756
WE CAN OFFER THE EXACT DESIGN YOU NEED
FOR YOUR POP-UP

727
00:59:53,839 --> 00:59:55,049
WE'LL SHOW YOU WHY SO MANY BRANDS
CHOSE US

728
00:59:55,132 --> 00:59:56,467
PERFECT EXHIBITION SPACE FOR THE BRAND,
FROM DESIGNING TO STYLING

729
01:00:05,309 --> 01:00:07,686
Why is the entrance covered in dirt?
Where were you?

730
01:00:07,770 --> 01:00:11,232
Oh, I'll hang this and clean it.

731
01:00:11,690 --> 01:00:14,151
And it's just a courteous thing
to tell your housemate

732
01:00:14,235 --> 01:00:17,696
when you're not coming home for the night.
It's a scary world out there.

733
01:00:17,780 --> 01:00:18,906
Oh, sorry.

734
01:00:18,989 --> 01:00:21,408
I had to make a last-minute trip
to Chuncheon for work

735
01:00:21,492 --> 01:00:22,618
and my phone turned off.

736
01:00:22,701 --> 01:00:26,247
I forgot to bring a charger
because it was so last minute.

737
01:00:26,747 --> 01:00:27,873
Sorry.

738
01:00:29,250 --> 01:00:30,334
Where's that hoodie from?

739
01:00:31,544 --> 01:00:33,671
This hoodie? What about it?

740
01:00:33,754 --> 01:00:35,381
It's just an oversized fit.

741
01:00:35,840 --> 01:00:39,051
Don't you know
oversized clothes are trending?

742
01:00:45,850 --> 01:00:48,727
I met them and tried to change their minds

743
01:00:48,978 --> 01:00:50,104
but it didn't work.

744
01:00:50,187 --> 01:00:51,730
Are you sure you tried?

745
01:00:51,814 --> 01:00:55,234
That's out of line.
She went to Chuncheon to convince them.

746
01:00:55,317 --> 01:00:56,819
That's true.

747
01:00:57,319 --> 01:01:01,365
We'll need some time to rebuild
a relationship with HOME.

748
01:01:01,448 --> 01:01:04,368
I'll focus on looking for a new company.

749
01:01:04,702 --> 01:01:07,413
Everyone's working overtime
until we settle on a new company.

750
01:01:07,746 --> 01:01:08,789
Fine.

751
01:01:11,876 --> 01:01:13,043
This is so stressful!

752
01:01:14,795 --> 01:01:15,880
Sorry.

753
01:01:16,046 --> 01:01:17,339
Don't be!

754
01:01:20,259 --> 01:01:21,719
It's okay, Sae-byeok.

755
01:01:22,845 --> 01:01:25,723
I made a new list of companies
we can contact.

756
01:01:25,806 --> 01:01:27,016
Let me share it with you.

757
01:01:27,099 --> 01:01:29,226
- Please do their background checks.
- Okay.

758
01:01:29,393 --> 01:01:31,729
And Hyun-min, let's divide the list
and contact them.

759
01:01:31,812 --> 01:01:33,439
Check if they're available first.

760
01:01:33,522 --> 01:01:35,900
Okay, give me the list,
and I'll go from the top.

761
01:01:35,983 --> 01:01:36,984
Perfect.

762
01:01:37,568 --> 01:01:38,611
Oh!

763
01:01:39,278 --> 01:01:41,363
I love this! Isn't it the best?

764
01:01:41,780 --> 01:01:43,699
I got the series second-hand
over the weekend.

765
01:01:43,782 --> 01:01:45,159
I hear it's a masterpiece.

766
01:01:45,242 --> 01:01:47,661
Yeah, once you start,
you won't stop until you're done.

767
01:01:47,870 --> 01:01:49,538
But you're still on the first book?

768
01:01:50,497 --> 01:01:52,666
Something even more exciting happened

769
01:01:52,750 --> 01:01:54,084
so I didn't have time to start.

770
01:01:54,460 --> 01:01:56,253
I wonder what that is.

771
01:01:57,671 --> 01:01:59,590
SONG TAE-SEOP

772
01:02:04,720 --> 01:02:06,013
Hello?

773
01:02:06,096 --> 01:02:07,681
Hi, Ui-yeong. It's me, Tae-seop.

774
01:02:07,973 --> 01:02:10,893
Yeah, what brings you to call me?

775
01:02:10,976 --> 01:02:14,104
Can we meet right now?
I have to tell you something important.

776
01:02:14,563 --> 01:02:15,940
I'll go to the hotel.

777
01:02:16,023 --> 01:02:17,650
Okay.

778
01:02:43,926 --> 01:02:45,803
What important thing does he need to say?

779
01:02:52,643 --> 01:02:54,186
SONG TAE-SEOP

780
01:02:54,270 --> 01:02:56,981
I'M HERE

781
01:02:57,064 --> 01:03:00,276
YOU CAN TAKE YOUR TIME

782
01:03:04,947 --> 01:03:06,865
Oh, hey, Ui-yeong!

783
01:03:06,949 --> 01:03:08,158
Hello.

784
01:03:08,284 --> 01:03:09,743
I hired someone new.

785
01:03:09,827 --> 01:03:11,704
- Really?
- I was busy training him.

786
01:03:11,787 --> 01:03:12,830
I see.

787
01:03:13,289 --> 01:03:15,582
- What would you like?
- A hot latte, please.

788
01:03:15,833 --> 01:03:17,167
A hot latte.

789
01:03:17,251 --> 01:03:19,878
So, did the other guy quit?

790
01:03:19,962 --> 01:03:22,423
He was so lazy.

791
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:24,967
I think I picked a good one this time.

792
01:03:25,050 --> 01:03:26,427
That's great!

793
01:03:27,261 --> 01:03:28,262
Here he comes.

794
01:03:29,555 --> 01:03:31,515
Say hi. She's a regular.

795
01:03:31,598 --> 01:03:33,058
She works at the hotel nearby.

796
01:03:35,728 --> 01:03:36,812
Ji-su!

797
01:03:37,271 --> 01:03:38,647
- What?
- Hi.

798
01:03:39,023 --> 01:03:40,357
You know each other?

799
01:03:40,441 --> 01:03:41,900
A little.

800
01:03:42,401 --> 01:03:43,444
What's going on?

801
01:03:43,527 --> 01:03:45,779
What are you doing here?

802
01:03:47,156 --> 01:03:48,157
Well...

803
01:04:21,732 --> 01:04:23,692
I really picked a good one.

804
01:04:28,572 --> 01:04:29,573
Here.

805
01:04:32,117 --> 01:04:34,578
Hey, how did you end up
getting a job here?

806
01:04:34,912 --> 01:04:36,663
The production is over

807
01:04:37,289 --> 01:04:39,958
and I got fired at the restaurant
for leaving without notice.

808
01:04:40,250 --> 01:04:41,502
I needed to make money.

809
01:04:41,585 --> 01:04:44,421
Oh, about the play
you invited me to last time.

810
01:04:44,505 --> 01:04:47,341
I couldn't go
because something urgent came up. Sorry.

811
01:04:47,549 --> 01:04:51,261
I was waiting for you,
thinking you might come late.

812
01:04:51,345 --> 01:04:52,721
But you never came.

813
01:04:53,055 --> 01:04:55,140
Oh, you waited for me?

814
01:04:56,975 --> 01:04:58,102
I'm kidding.

815
01:04:58,477 --> 01:05:00,729
We can't even see the audience
from the stage, anyway.

816
01:05:01,772 --> 01:05:04,358
I act for a living.
I'll have more productions coming.

817
01:05:04,900 --> 01:05:06,944
Come next time. I'll get you a ticket.

818
01:05:07,027 --> 01:05:08,987
Okay, then. Thanks.

819
01:05:10,906 --> 01:05:13,784
Let's eat together, then.
Once to apologize, and once to say thanks.

820
01:05:13,867 --> 01:05:15,327
You can treat me twice.

821
01:05:17,913 --> 01:05:18,914
Hey

822
01:05:19,164 --> 01:05:22,334
shouldn't you apologize to me first?

823
01:05:22,751 --> 01:05:23,752
Yeah.

824
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:26,547
But you can't take back what you said.

825
01:05:27,214 --> 01:05:30,008
You're determined to leech off of me, huh?

826
01:05:30,592 --> 01:05:31,844
What about tomorrow evening?

827
01:05:31,927 --> 01:05:33,637
I'm working until closing tonight.

828
01:05:34,430 --> 01:05:35,514
Tomorrow...

829
01:05:35,597 --> 01:05:36,598
Ui-yeong.

830
01:05:38,058 --> 01:05:39,435
Oh, hi, Tae-seop.

831
01:05:44,523 --> 01:05:45,858
Don't tell me he remembers him.

832
01:05:45,941 --> 01:05:47,943
So, we meet again, Ui-yeong's cousin.

833
01:05:52,072 --> 01:05:54,450
This feels awfully familiar.

834
01:05:54,992 --> 01:05:57,786
Is it time for us to head out now?

835
01:05:59,746 --> 01:06:01,165
No, it's not.

836
01:06:14,386 --> 01:06:15,471
About yesterday.

837
01:06:16,722 --> 01:06:18,056
Yesterday?

838
01:06:18,557 --> 01:06:20,350
Yeah, when we kissed.

839
01:06:21,810 --> 01:06:24,396
- What?
- I was so excited to see you again

840
01:06:24,730 --> 01:06:26,440
that I couldn't even sleep at night.

841
01:06:29,568 --> 01:06:30,694
Did you sleep well?

842
01:06:48,128 --> 01:06:51,048
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

843
01:06:53,342 --> 01:06:55,385
WE ALWAYS HAVE BAD TIMING

844
01:06:56,845 --> 01:06:58,388
YOU LOOK LIKE AN APPLE

845
01:06:59,890 --> 01:07:01,892
I CAN'T STOP THINKING ABOUT YOU,
EVEN IN THIS MOMENT

846
01:07:06,688 --> 01:07:08,774
THE LEFT HAND IS JUST FOR SUPPORT

847
01:07:13,612 --> 01:07:16,073
IF THIS IS A SIN, I'LL REPENT LATER

848
01:07:23,997 --> 01:07:24,998
Do...

849
01:07:26,458 --> 01:07:27,584
what together?

850
01:07:27,834 --> 01:07:29,586
The ki...

851
01:07:30,295 --> 01:07:33,131
You can't just stop talking, you dumbass!

852
01:07:33,215 --> 01:07:34,508
So, are you two dating now?

853
01:07:35,050 --> 01:07:36,385
- Hey!
- What are you, 20?

854
01:07:36,468 --> 01:07:37,761
One kiss, and you're all his?

855
01:07:37,844 --> 01:07:40,097
I really like you.

856
01:07:41,223 --> 01:07:43,016
- You jerk!
- Use your words!

857
01:07:43,100 --> 01:07:44,601
We got our idea today...

858
01:07:44,685 --> 01:07:45,936
Maybe after work...

859
01:07:46,353 --> 01:07:48,230
I feel so refreshed now!

860
01:07:48,313 --> 01:07:50,816
You're so close to me

861
01:07:51,316 --> 01:07:54,653
yet I can't reach you.
That drives me crazy.

862
01:07:56,280 --> 01:07:58,323
Did I sleep with him?

863
01:08:05,998 --> 01:08:08,000
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
